text: Tripylella muscusi is a species of nematodes, first found in Mexico. It can be distinguished by its body length (averaging ); its pharynx and tail lengths; its possession of an excretory pore; exhibiting body pores and scant somatic setae; a striated cuticle carrying sparse anastomoses; as well as protruding vulval lips, among other characteristics.DEL PRADO-VERA, IGNACIO CID, Howard Ferris, and Steven A. Nadler. "Five new species of the genus Tripylella (Nematoda: Enoplida: Tripylidae)."Zootaxa 4109.2 (2016): 198-217. == References == Category:Enoplia
title: Tripylella muscusi
